Available Commands:
  Data:        USE, SAVE, RUN, NEW, NAMES, WRITE, DELETE, DISPLAY
  Variables:   LET, SET, UNSET, HOLD, UNHOLD, KEEP, DROP, RENAME
  Arrays:      ARRAY, DIM
  Control:     IF, SELECT CASE, FOR, WHILE, REPEAT, BREAK
  Data step:   SELECT (filter), SELECT /ALL, BY, SORT, AGGREGATE, REPEAT
  Output:      PRINT, OUTPUT, ECHO, DIGITS
  Files/paths: FPATH
  Session:     RSEED, SYSTEM, SUBMIT, HELP, OPTIONS, QUIT, END
  Debugger:    BREAK, BREAK WHEN  (see also: HELP DEBUGGER for --debug mode)

Available Functions:
  Math:        ABS, SQRT/SQR, LOG/LN/LOGE, LOG2, LOG10/CLG/LGT, EXP,
               ROUND, CEIL, FLOOR, INT, FIX/IP, FP/FRAC, MOD, SGN,
               TRUNCATE, PI, LTW
  Trig (rad):  SIN, COS, TAN, ATN/ARCTAN, ATAN2, ARCSIN, ARCCOS,
               COT, CSC, SEC, SINH/HSN, COSH/HCS, TANH/HTN, DEG/DEGREE,
               RAD/RADIAN
  Trig (deg):  SIND, COSD, TAND, ATND, ATAN2D
  String:      LEN, LEFT$, RIGHT$, MID$, SEG$, TRIM$, LTRIM$, RTRIM$,
               UCASE$/UPPER$, LCASE$/LOWER$, POS, INSTR, INDEX, MATCH,
               CHR$, ASCII/ASC, STR$, VAL, NUM$, MAXLEN
  Conversion:  NUM, HEX, HEX$, OCT$, BIN$
  Arrays:      LBOUND, UBOUND, HBOUND
  Record:      RECNO, BOF, EOF, BOG, EOG, LAG, LAGC$, NEXT, NEXTC$, OBS, OBSC$
  Special:     MISSING, INF, NMISS, RAN/RANDOM/RND, DATE$, TIME$, TIMER, SHELL,
               FALSE, TRUE, ERR, ERL,
               MAXINT, MININT, MAXNUM, MINNUM, MAXLVL
  Aggregate:   SUM, MEAN, GMEAN, HMEAN, STD, VAR, MIN, MAX, MEDIAN, N, NMISS
  Stat PDF:    ZDF, NDF, UDF, EDF, BDF, PDF, GDF, XDF, TDF, FDF,
               MDF, WDF, LDF
  Stat CDF:    ZCF, NCF, UCF, ECF, BCF, PCF, GCF, XCF, TCF, FCF,
               MCF, WCF, LCF
  Stat IDF:    ZIF, NIF, UIF, EIF, BIF, GIF, XIF, TIF, FIF, WIF,
               LIF, PIF
  Stat RN:     ZRN, NRN, URN, ERN, PRN, GRN, MRN, XRN, TRN,
               FRN, WRN, LRN, RAN, RANDOM
  (Use HELP DISTRIBUTIONS for an overview of naming conventions.)

Use HELP <name> for details.  Use HELP /ALL for the full reference.
Use HELP EXECUTION for an explanation of the three execution tiers.
Use HELP CONCEPTS for an introduction to the PDV, LET/SET, BY groups, and quoted identifiers.
